^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|First of all let's see if I should consider a club slam, and how might bid it with an expert partner. 6C by South is an excellent slam (it happens to go down because of the unlucky club break). But 6C by North is not nearly as good. The reason it is better if played by South is because of the hearts. If South is playing the hand, then the @HK is protected. |
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Even if the opponents lead hearts, N/S have only 1 immediate heart loser if played by South. But if played by North, with a heart lead, East has to have the @HA in order for the slam to make. So this hand illustrates the principle that sometimes who declares makes a big difference. 6C by South only depends on a 2-1 club break which is somewhere around 85%. In fact, if East has 3 clubs, it still makes, as East can be finessed. So it  is upward of 90% to make.|
PG| ***** 19 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The way I would get there is—the way I play—all 3 level bids over 1NT are natural and slam invitational. This is very non-standard, but I am not sure why, as I have gotten to many slams using this approach. So I would bid 3C, which is a slam invite with a 6-card or good 5-card suit. If the NT bidder has good support (3 to an honor), they start control bidding. If not they bid 3N, saying they do not have good support.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So the auction with my partners would start 1N-3C. North should then fall in love with her hand. Great club support, lots of controls, great HCP, nothing wasted. The only issue is the heart suit. So over 3C the auction should go 3D (@DK) 3H by South (@HK) 3S by North (@SA). Now I know we have all suits controlled and bid 4N with a minor suit as trump. |
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Even if you usually play 1430 you should play 0314 here with a minor suit being trump. Unfortunately, due to the very unlikely club break it goes down, but it is definitely a slam I want to be in (unless I peeked in the west hand :) ). So the complete auction is you will see next.|
